article.headline: Dayton 38, Davidson 28
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Jack O'Dell caught three touchdown passes to tie a Dayton record while Kevin Hoyng threw for 408 yards as the Flyers beat Davidson, 38-28, on Saturday as both teams combined for exactly 1,000 total yards. Two of O'Dell's touchdowns came in the last 2:18 of the first half, and put Dayton (6-1, 2-1 Pioneer Football League) ahead 21-14. Davidson (3-3, 1-2) evened it up in the third quarter with a 14-play, 73-yard drive that ended on a 2-yard Kenny Mantuo run. Two minutes later, Hoyng threw his fourth touchdown of the game -- a 13-yarder to Nick Ruhe -- and Dayton stayed in front from there. Hoyng was 25-for-40 with one interception. He also rushed for 77 yards on 15 carries, and his 408 passing yards were the third-most ever for a Dayton quarterback. Ruhe led Flyers receivers with nine receptions for 160 yards. Davidson's Ryan Hubbard had 10 catches for 138 yards, while Mantuo, Chad Barnes and Ryan Alexander combined to churn out 174 rushing yards for the Wildcats.
